        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39687",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "* One of your validators is used wrong\r\n\r\n* Loading the form from cache something is wrong. The returned failure is from PHP. In detail $_FILES[xxx]['error'] is set to 1 instead of 0. ZF just returns a usefull description instead of an integer value.\r\n\r\nLook what $_FILES does... this could help you to debug your code.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-31T14:01:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-31T14:01:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39692",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=storeman",
                        "name": "storeman",
                        "displayName": "Martin Winkel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've removed the validators. The error still occurs.\r\n\r\nHave you seen my demo? I've added the _FILES data, it seems ok. The errorcode is 4, which is valid, because I don't upload anything.\r\n\r\nTry uploading no file, this shouldn't give an error, unless required is set to true.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=storeman",
                        "name": "storeman",
                        "displayName": "Martin Winkel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-31T14:54:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-31T14:54:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39781",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Tried your demo several (~40) times empty and ~10 times with Fileupload,\r\nthere was no error for me, does this mean you found a solution for your problem,\r\nand this issue could be closed?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-03T17:11:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-03T17:11:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39786",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=storeman",
                        "name": "storeman",
                        "displayName": "Martin Winkel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You're right, the problem doesn't occur anymore. When I add the Size validator, it does. Can you verify this?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=storeman",
                        "name": "storeman",
                        "displayName": "Martin Winkel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-04T03:29:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-04T03:29:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39787",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "what happens if you do not clone $form, but save it directly to cache?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-04T04:08:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-04T04:08:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39789",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Answer to myself the same error, but the displayed message \"File 'file' exceeds the defined ini size\"\r\nis defined in Zend_Validate_File_Upload and not in Zend_Validate_File_Size.\r\n\r\nAnd it is displayed because the Transfer Adapter sets the error to int(1) in\r\n{code:title=Zend_File_Transfer_Adapter_Http isValid()}\r\n    public function isValid($files = null)\r\n    {\r\n        \/\/ Workaround for WebServer not conforming HTTP and omitting CONTENT_LENGTH\r\n        $content = 0;\r\n        if (isset($_SERVER['CONTENT_LENGTH'])) {\r\n            $content = $_SERVER['CONTENT_LENGTH'];\r\n        } else if (!empty($_POST)) {\r\n            $content = serialize($_POST);\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        \/\/ Workaround for a PHP error returning empty $_FILES when form data exceeds php settings\r\n        if (empty($this->_files) && ($content > 0)) {\r\n            if (is_array($files)) {\r\n                $files = current($files);\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            $temp = array($files => array(\r\n                'name'  => $files,\r\n                'error' => 1));\r\n            $validator = $this->_validators['Zend_Validate_File_Upload'];\r\n            $validator->setFiles($temp)\r\n                      ->isValid($files, null);\r\n            $this->_messages += $validator->getMessages();\r\n            return false;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        return parent::isValid($files);\r\n    }\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-04T05:09:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-04T05:09:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39790",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Added appropriate Components",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-04T05:17:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-04T05:17:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39791",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think now this ones real issue is Zend_Form_Element_File not setting up \r\n$adapter->_files when loading the Form from cache and that makes Adapters\r\nisValid method add the error 1 to the filename.\r\n\r\nWhen not loading from cache $adapter->_files is filled with array('file' => ...)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-04T05:58:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-04T05:58:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39794",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I never said that it's within the Size validator.\r\nI knew that it's the Upload validator. That's the reason why I asked you for the content of $_FILES.\r\n\r\nLooking at your online example there ARE differences.\r\n\r\nWhy is $_FILES different when you send it and when you load it from cache?\r\n\r\nThe code block you referred to prevents a PHP problem.\r\nThe only way how it can run into this block is when $_FILES is empty and $_SERVER['CONTENT_LENGTH'] is not empty. PHP itself has a problem when one of it's settings is lower than the provided POST content.\r\n\r\nI don't think that it's a problem of the component because the component reacts only on the input from $_POST, $_FILES and some $_SERVER settings. When the cached data differs then also the output differs.\r\n\r\nNote that when you are caching the input, it's also possible that you get an \"attacker\" exception.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-04T09:16:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-04T09:16:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39795",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Note that the file element is not set to be optional.\r\nSo raising an failure when no file is given is correct behaviour.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-04T09:23:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-04T09:23:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39796",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks for the journey into Zend_File ;P\r\nThis can not work as you expect because Zend_File_Transfer_Adapter_Http\r\n_prepareFiles() within and only within __construct() from Global $_FILES.\r\n\r\nSo you will always end up serializing the Adapter with $_FILES at time\r\nof saving to cache.\r\n\r\nWhich is either empty and generates this messages in conclusion, or is\r\nfilled with the at-save-time uploaded $_FILES metadata, and thus generates an \r\nAttack Error because the actual file data for the saved $_FILES is missing.\r\n\r\nWorkaround, add to your Form class:\r\n{code}\r\npublic function __wakeup()\r\n{\r\n   $this->init();\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\nor call it after loading $form from cache with $form->init();\r\n\r\nThomas, what do you think, could this be closed now?\r\nOr should we make a Feature Request for the ability to store\r\nForms with File Elements in cache?\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-04T09:32:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-04T09:49:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39797",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Closing as non-issue.\r\n\r\n$_FILES content is different before saving and after loading from cache.\r\nThe file adapter is therefor not able to work.\r\n\r\nThe only solution is to create a new instance of Zend_File_Transfer and add it to the element AFTER it has been loaded from cache and BEFORE running validation.\r\n\r\nNote that PHP itself does not allow to cache temporary uploaded files.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-04T10:01:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-04T10:01:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39798",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=storeman",
                        "name": "storeman",
                        "displayName": "Martin Winkel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I do not want to cache input or tempfiles, I want to cache the form structure as build in the init. I load the form form cache and use it to validate _POST or to set defaults and allow users to change it.\r\n\r\nI know understand the issue and can create a work-around for it. Isn't it possible to add a _wakeup method to the Zend_Form_Element_File and reinit only that element?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=storeman",
                        "name": "storeman",
                        "displayName": "Martin Winkel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-04T10:45:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-04T10:45:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39815",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=storeman",
                        "name": "storeman",
                        "displayName": "Martin Winkel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The following solves my problem:\r\n\r\n[code]\r\n    public function __wakeup(){\r\n    \t$this->_adapter = null;\r\n    }\r\n[\/code]\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=storeman",
                        "name": "storeman",
                        "displayName": "Martin Winkel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-05T06:48:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-05T06:48:15.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
